# Testing

## Runner and config

- Unit and integration tests use **Vitest** (`vitest.config.mts` at repo root).
- Path aliases match app code; prefer existing test utilities and helpers over ad-hoc setup.

## Commands (repo root)

| Command | Use |
|--------|-----|
| `yarn test` / `yarn test:app` | Watch mode during development |
| `yarn test:app --watch=false` | Single run, no watch |
| `yarn test:update` | Refresh snapshots (`--update` on Vitest) — run only when you intentionally changed outputs; not for routine verification |
| `yarn test:typecheck` | TypeScript (`tsc`) |
| `yarn test:all` | Full gate: typecheck, eslint, prettier, app tests (no watch) |
| `yarn test:coverage` | Coverage report |

After `yarn test:app --watch=false` reports snapshot failures you accept, use `yarn test:update` to record them; see `AGENTS.md` for the repo’s pre-commit test workflow.

## Where tests live

- **Colocated**: `ComponentName.test.tsx` next to the component (preferred for components; see `conventions.mdc`).
- **Package suites**: e.g. `packages/excalidraw/tests/`, `packages/element/tests/`, `excalidraw-app/tests/` for broader scenarios.

Follow the pattern already used in the nearest directory.

## Quality bar

- Do not delete or gut assertions to make tests pass; fix behavior or update snapshots only when the new output is correct.
- Do not use `@ts-ignore` or `any` in tests to hide type problems.
- If you change rendering or UI that affects snapshots, run `yarn test:app --watch=false` to see failures, then `yarn test:update` and review diffs carefully.

## Protected areas

Changes under protected files (see `do-not-touch.mdc`) require the full test suite and manual verification — treat regressions there as high risk.

## How to verify

- From the repo root, run `yarn test:typecheck`, then `yarn test:app --watch=false` (non-mutating). Run `yarn test:update` only when snapshot changes are expected and you intend to refresh snapshots — not as the default first check.
- Before commit, prefer `yarn test:all` for the full gate (typecheck, lint, format check, tests).
- If snapshots changed, re-read the snapshot diffs to ensure only intended visual or output changes are recorded.
